            <div class="title col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2"><h1>Proposal</h1></div>
            <div class="paragraph col-xs-12 col-sm-12 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2"><p><i>Flux</i> is a near-future energy service provider that supplies this equipment in a monthly leasing contract. As part of the contract, customers buy energy in terms of applications - like wash cycles or car charges - rather than kilowatt hours, using a more understandable language for energy usage. The <i>Flux</i> energy management system features both a physical and digital user interface. A physical device - <i>Ele</i> - ambiently displays energy used against an AI generated daily budget, to help users stay within their monthly tariff. The <i>Flux</i> App offers a more detailed breakdown of energy usage and centralises the control of devices.</p></div>
